Cell.Text: The bow was said to be carried by Auri-El himself into battle against the forces of Lorkhan in ancient and mythic times. | Its craftsmanship has no equal anywhere within Tamriel and possibly beyond.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ07PostGeleborBowBranchTopic: What can you tell me about Auriel's Bow?

Cell.Text: The bow draws its power from Aetherius itself, channeling it through the sun. | Therefore, when an arrow is loosed from the bow, it produces a magical effect very similar to being burned by fire.

[S] That's actually only a fraction of its potential. | With Sunhallowed Arrows, you would be able to produce a much more spectacular effect... causing bursts of sunlight to envelop your foes. | The sunbursts would certainly hurt anything, but is especially devastating to the undead.
Well, using an arrow with the bow that's been dipped in blood may cause it to function differently... corrupting its purpose. | That's of course if you're foolish enough to try it.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ07PostGeleborBowBranchTopic03: Vyrthur said something about using blood?

Cell.Text: S|I can actually assist you in that regard. | If you were to bring me some good quality elven arrows, I could imbue them with the proper incantations and rituals.
Can you make me some Sunhallowed Arrows?
I'm afraid I'll need elven arrows if you want me to produce the Sunhallowed Arrows, and it seems you're all out of them at the moment.
Can you make me some Sunhallowed Arrows?
[S] Certainly. I can only do twenty at a time, but I see that won't be a problem in this case.
Can you make me some Sunhallowed Arrows?
[S] Absolutely. I can only do twenty at a time, so if you want the rest of your arrows blessed, let me know.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ07PostGeleborArrowsBranchTopic: How do I obtain Sunhallowed Arrows?

Cell.Text: While it would fill me with joy to see the Chantry back to its former glory, that time has long since passed. | It's quite possible that Arch-Curate Vyrthur was the last of our kind.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ07PostGeleborChantryBranchTopic: What will happen to the Chantry now?

Cell.Text: There's no need for that kind of talk. I said it was possible. | It's also quite possible that there are some other isolated conclaves of snow elves nestled elsewhere on Nirn. | I'll also assume Vyrthur didn't exactly give you the option to stay your hand.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ07PostGeleborChantryBranchTopic01: Then I'm responsible for your kind's extinction.

Cell.Text: For the time being I will remain here, on the overlook and continue trying to keep the Sanctum free of the Betrayed. | You're always welcome to return here at any time, of course.
I feel nothing but sympathy for the Betrayed, despite my actions against them. | But I'm afraid that they're well beyond a cure at this point.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ07PostGeleborBetrayedBranchTopic: Can the Betrayed ever be cured?

Cell.Text: The twisted forms you've seen didn't occur overnight. It isn't a plague or a disease that ravaged our species. | The dwarves may have stolen their sight, but it took many generations for them to become what they are today.

Perhaps they'll never return to their former appearance, but over the centuries, I've noticed a rise in their intellect. | If a line of communication could be established with them, maybe they can find peace. | It's the only way they'll discover that they weren't always malignant... they were once a proud and prosperous race.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ07PostGeleborBetrayedBranchTopic02: Then there's no hope for them.
